channel.title: Default IP Adress
channel.description:
Ok, I've looked at many different tutorials showing me how to make my own server. I understand everything I have to do but my computer isn't really working for me. When I go to the CMD, I type in "ipconfig".. I even tried "all" and "ipconfig/all". The only thing that pops up afterwards is: "" is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file. SOO I went to No-Ip.com and it shows me one of my Ip's, I type it into the browser, and nothing loads! :(
Can someone help please :(.

item.title: Default IP Adress
item.dc:creator: @Fireweaver0 Fireweaver0
item.description:
@Fireweaver0 wrote:

No problem.

The variables you change for Environment variables are your USER variables.
So just make the two variables in USER not in SYSTEM.

item.description:
@Aleksander wrote:

Thank you so much :)!

Now, that creates a new question lol. In the tutorials… I had to change two paths under Environmental Variables, if wasn’t one of them, which was it? I already have CLASSPATH changed.

item.title: Default IP Adress
item.dc:creator: @Fireweaver0 Fireweaver0
item.description:
@Fireweaver0 wrote:

You need to fix your Path in Environment Variables.
Go back to your environment variables and under SYSTEM variables make sure your Path value is this

C:\WINDOWS\system32

Then do the ipconfig/all again.

Read full topic
